# Prisma Schema Conventions

The dashboard owns the Prisma schema — the single source of truth for the PostgreSQL database.

## Rules

- Every domain table MUST have a `tenantId` field (FK to Tenant) for multi-tenant isolation
- Use `@@map("snake_case")` for table names, camelCase for Prisma model fields
- All IDs are `String @id @default(cuid())` (CUID for distributed safety)
- Timestamps: `createdAt DateTime @default(now())`, `updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt`
- Enums for status fields: define as Prisma `enum` (e.g., `AlertStatus`, `CaseStatus`, `Severity`)
- AuditLog is append-only: no `updatedAt`, no update/delete operations in code
- Indexes: always index `tenantId` + frequently filtered fields (status, createdAt)
- After schema changes: `npx prisma migrate dev --name descriptive_name`

## Case Status Enum (state machine)
Detected → Open → Investigating → Awaiting_Approval → Contained → Closed
(Awaiting_Approval → Investigating is valid for approval grants)

## Alert Status Enum
New → Triaged → Closed_FP → Escalated
